de.boereck.matcher.helpers

Class StringMatchHelpers

  • java.lang.Object
    • de.boereck.matcher.helpers.StringMatchHelpers

  • public final class StringMatchHelpers
extends Object
    Provides static helper functions for defining matches in CaseMatchers based on String values.

    This class is not intended to be instantiated or sub-classed.

      • matching

        public static OptionalMapper<String,String> matching(String regEx)
                                              throws NullPointerException,
                                                     PatternSyntaxException
        Returns a function mapping from String to Optional&lt;String&gt;, based on the given regular expression regEx. The returned function will return an empty optional if the input string to the function does not match the given regular expression. If the regular expression does match, the returned optional will contain the input string.
        Parameters:
        regEx - regular expression that is being checked in the returned function. Must not be null.
        Returns:
        function mapping from String to Optional&lt;String&gt;, based on the given regular expression regEx.
        Throws:
        NullPointerException - thrown, if regEx is null.
        PatternSyntaxException - if expression syntax of regEx is invalid.

      • matcher

        public static OptionalMapper<String,Matcher> matcher(String regEx)
                                              throws NullPointerException,
                                                     PatternSyntaxException
        Returns a function mapping from String to Optional&lt;Matcher&gt;, based on the given regular expression regEx. The returned function will return an empty optional if the input string to the function does not match the given regular expression. If the regular expression does match, the returned optional will contain the Matcher that is the result of the input string matching against regular expression regEx.
        Parameters:
        regEx - regular expression that is being checked in the returned function. Must not be null.
        Returns:
        function mapping from String to Optional&lt;Matcher&gt;, based on the given regular expression regEx.
        Throws:
        NullPointerException - thrown, if regEx is null.
        PatternSyntaxException - if expression syntax of regEx is invalid.

      • split

        public static OptionalMapper<String,String[]> split(String regEx)
                                             throws PatternSyntaxException,
                                                    NullPointerException
        Returns a function that takes string and splits it according to the regular expression regEx. Tf the input to the function is null, the returned Optional will be empty, otherwise the returned Optional will contain an array of strings computed from the splitting of the input string.

        This method or the returned method may throw an PatternSyntaxException if the regular expression's syntax is invalid

        Parameters:
        regEx - the delimiting regular expression for splitting the input array. Must not be null.
        Returns:
        function splitting an input string according to parameter regEx
        Throws:
        PatternSyntaxException - May be thrown if regEx' syntax is invalid.
        NullPointerException - thrown, if regEx is null.

      • split

        public static OptionalMapper<String,String[]> split(String regEx,
                                                    int limit)
                                             throws NullPointerException,
                                                    PatternSyntaxException
        Returns a function that takes string and splits it according to the regular expression regEx. Tf the input to the function is null, the returned Optional will be empty, otherwise the returned Optional will contain an array of strings computed from the splitting of the input string. The input string will be split in at most as many elements as specified in parameter limit. This affects the length of the array returned from the split.

        This method or the returned method may throw an PatternSyntaxException if the regular expression's syntax is invalid

        Parameters:
        regEx - the delimiting regular expression for splitting the input array
        limit - maximum amount of elements in result of split
        Returns:
        function splitting an input string according to parameter regEx
        Throws:
        PatternSyntaxException - May be thrown if the expression's syntax is invalid
        NullPointerException - thrown, if regEx is null.
